title._content: Keene High School (old) Graduating Class of 1875, Keene, New Hampshire

description._content: TITLE Keene High School (old) Graduating Class of 1875, Keene, New Hampshire CREATOR French, J.A., Keene NH SUBJECT Schools - NH - Keene Students - NH - Keene DESCRIPTION Stereograph of the Keene High School Graduating Class of 1875, Keene, New Hampshire in front of the old Keene High School building? It was built in 1875 on Winter Street (where the parking lot is now) and served as the high school from 1875 to 1915. From 1915 to 1953, it was the Central Junior High School. It was torn down in 1956. If this is the same as the other photo, and it appears to be, then the students' names are as follows: Helen M. Howard, Nellie L. Todd, Charles E. Richards, Nellie I. Priest, Elmon H. Gilbert, Frank G. Dort, Emma W. Richards, Etta M. Humphrey, Nan L. Hart, Ira J. Prouty, Flora E. Sargent, Eugene L. Willard, Julia D. Hatch, Isabella S. Spaulding, Fred E. Barrett, Helen F. Haskell, Ella F. Marshall, and Charles S. Cook. Handwritten: S.H. Brackett, Prin.(?) PUBLISHER Keene Public Library and the Historical Society of Cheshire County DATE DIGITAL 20091221 DATE ORIGINAL 1875 RESOURCE TYPE stereographs FORMAT image/jpg RESOURCE IDENTIFIER HS352-P3056 RIGHTS MANAGMENT No known copyright restrictions.
